'''''-li''''' is a partitive plural ending in [[Quenya]], indicating "many, some, a lot of".<ref name=Eldarin>{{PE|Eldarin}}</ref>{{rp|62}}

==Etymology==
[[Root]] LI-, meaning "many", from which ''[[lië]]'' also comes.<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, entry "LI-"</ref> Compare ''-lai'' in ''[[Kinn-lai]]''.

==Examples==
*''vanimá'''li'''on'' = genitive "of beautiful children"<ref>{{L|230}}, p. 308, cf. note 5</ref>
*i ''[[falma]]-'''li'''-nna-r'' = "the foam wave-many-towards-pl. ending"<ref name=Eldarin />{{rp|127}}

